<MudGrid Spacing="4" Justify="Justify.SpaceEvenly">
    <MudItem xs="4">
        <MudText Typo="@Typo.h5">Gaining Wealth</MudText>
        <br />
        <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
            When characters perform actions that would increase their Wealth, instead of earning explicit amounts of gold 
            or other currency, they progress towards the next level of Wealth.
            <br /><br />
            To ascend from one level to another, characters must undertake significant quests, find treasures, invest 
            in businesses, or receive massive rewards. The jump between levels should represent substantial growth in their Wealth.
        </MudText>
    </MudItem>
    <MudItem xs="4">
        <MudText Typo="@Typo.h5">Losing Wealth</MudText>
        <br />
        <MudText Typo="@Typo.body1">
            Major expenses, robberies, disasters, or bad investments can cause characters to lose Wealth levels. 
            If a character loses the last Wealth Level in a Tier, their Wealth drops down one Tier.
            <br /><br />
            For example, having 1 Chest of Wealth and spending it would drop the character's Wealth Level to 4 Bags of Wealth.
        </MudText>
    </MudItem>
</MudGrid>

